Title: Move fast, but understand the problem first
Description:
Startup founders need to do two things: (1) figure out what to do, (2) do it.
(I suppose that applies to anyone, but I'm writing about founders). My beef
with "move fast" is that I don't naturally associate it with figuring out what
to do. To me, "move" is physical, outward, observable. Shipping features and
talking to people... but not thinking. If I spent a day thinking, trying to
better understand a problem, I wouldn't view myself as having "moved fast" that
day. And that's a real shame, at least if "good founders move fast" is true.
